==============
 Hydrogeology
==============

:status: hidden


Hydrogeology (ERS 480/580) covers groundwater flow and water chemistry in the subsurface saturated zone. Specific topics include Darcy's Law, interpreting hydraulic head data, piezometer tests, pumping tests, and solute transport. I plan to enhance this page to include information on these topics. A `syllabus <{static}../../images/ERS580_syllabus.pdf>`_ may be reviewed that outlines the structure of this class and topics covered.

